In [[Hinduism]] and [[Buddhism]], '''arūpa''' (a Sanskrit word) refers to formless (perhaps non-physical) or also non-material objects or subjects.  [[Aether (classical element)|Ether]] ([[akasha]] in Sanskrit) is somewhat arūpa, while the [[classical elements]] are [[rupa (Buddhism)|rupa]].<ref>[http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/37413/arupa-loka arūpa-loka - Britannica Online Encyclopedia<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>

