'''Nelly Longarms''' (or '''Nellie Longarms''') is a [[hag]] and [[water spirit]] in [[English folklore]] who dwells at the bottom of deep ponds, rivers and wells. Like the [[Grindylow]], [[Peg Powler]] and [[Jenny Greenteeth]] she will reach out with her long sinewy arms and drag children beneath the water if they get too close. She is regarded as a [[bogeyman]] figure who is invoked by parents to frighten children into proper behaviour.<ref>Briggs, Katharine (1976). ''An Encyclopedia of Fairies''. Pantheon Books. p. 305. {{ISBN|0394409183}}.</ref><ref>Wright, Elizabeth Mary (1913). ''Rustic Speech and Folk-Lore''. Humphrey Milford, Oxford University Press. pp. 198-199.</ref><ref name=Bane>Bane, Theresa (2013). ''Encyclopedia of Fairies in World Folklore and Mythology''. McFarland & Co. p. 245. {{ISBN|0786471115}}.</ref>

