'''Pudhota Chinniah Balaswamy''' (10 October 1928 – 24 September 2009) was the [[India]]n [[bishop]] of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Nellore]], which is based in the city of [[Nellore]]. Bishop Balaswamy served as the Bishop of Nellore from 17 December 1973, until his retirement on 7 December 2006.

Bishop Pudhota Chinniah Balaswamy was born in [[Valarpuram]] and ordained a [[Roman Catholic priest]] on 24 April 1955.  He died on 24 September 2009, at the age of 81.

